page.title: 20School Camp,Mundesley,1985
page.content: shopping in the morning and to the swimming pool in the afternoon.The swimming pool had a diving board and we kept jumping off.In the evening we took part in football and rounders competitions.We lost in the finals of both. On Tuesday we shopped in Mundesley and played on the beach and in the park.In the evening there was a fancy dress competition and some of us dressed up. On Wednesday we had to pack up our things ready to come home.We set off from Mundesley at half past eleven and got home at quarter past six. Although the weather wasn't very good we enjoyed ourselves,but we were pleased to be home. Louise Holmes Lisa Salt Matthew Fletcher
